import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.axhline(y=data['price'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean Price: {data['price'].mean():.2f}")
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average price of stocks over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.sort_values(by='price', ascending=False)
    sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.axhline(y=data['price'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Price: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].max()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Which stock had the highest price?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'] = pd.to_numeric(data['price'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['price'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of stock prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    data = data.groupby(['symbol']).mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data)
    chart.axhline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', label='Average Price')
    chart.set(xlabel='Symbol', ylabel='Average Price')
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
